net.hudup.core.data

Interface AutoCloseable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    CTSManager, ExternalQuery, Fetcher<E>, Provider, ProviderAssoc, UriAssoc
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BitData, CTSManagerAbstract, DatasetSampler, Datasource, DefaultCTSManager, DefaultExternalQuery, DefaultService, MemFetcher, MetaFetcher, ProviderAssocAbstract, ProviderImpl, UriAdapter, UriAdapter.AdapterWriteChannel, UriAssocAbstract

    public interface AutoCloseable
    This interface establishes the rule that all classes which implements AutoCloseable has a mechanism of auto-closing. The main method of this interface is close(). The class that implements this interface is called auto-closable class. The common implementation of close() method is to release resources occupied by auto-closable object. The finalize() method of auto-closable class should call close() method. Concretely, if programmer forgets closing auto-closable object to release resources after using such object, the close() is automatically called by the finalize() to close release resources before the Java garbage collector destroys such object.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen
